com.intercom.base

类 CommandLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intercom.base.CommandLine

  • public abstract class CommandLine
extends java.lang.Object
    Java mirror of base/command_line.h. Android applications don't have command line arguments. Instead, they're "simulated" by reading a file at a specific location early during startup. Applications each define their own files, e.g., ContentShellApplication.COMMAND_LINE_FILE.

    • 嵌套类概要

      嵌套类 
      限定符和类型 类和说明
      static interface  CommandLine.ResetListener
      Allows classes who cache command line flags to be notified when those arguments are updated at runtime.

    • 方法详细资料

      • hasSwitch

        public abstract boolean hasSwitch(java.lang.String switchString)
        Returns true if this command line contains the given switch. (Switch names ARE case-sensitive).

      • getSwitchValue

        public abstract java.lang.String getSwitchValue(java.lang.String switchString)
        Return the value associated with the given switch, or null.
        参数:
        switchString - The switch key to lookup. It should NOT start with '--' !
        返回:
        switch value, or null if the switch is not set or set to empty.

      • getSwitchValue

        public java.lang.String getSwitchValue(java.lang.String switchString,
                                       java.lang.String defaultValue)
        Return the value associated with the given switch, or defaultValue if the switch was not specified.
        参数:
        switchString - The switch key to lookup. It should NOT start with '--' !
        defaultValue - The default value to return if the switch isn't set.
        返回:
        Switch value, or defaultValue if the switch is not set or set to empty.

      • appendSwitch

        public abstract void appendSwitch(java.lang.String switchString)
        Append a switch to the command line. There is no guarantee this action happens before the switch is needed.
        参数:
        switchString - the switch to add. It should NOT start with '--' !

      • appendSwitchWithValue

        public abstract void appendSwitchWithValue(java.lang.String switchString,
                                           java.lang.String value)
        Append a switch and value to the command line. There is no guarantee this action happens before the switch is needed.
        参数:
        switchString - the switch to add. It should NOT start with '--' !
        value - the value for this switch. For example, --foo=bar becomes 'foo', 'bar'.

      • appendSwitchesAndArguments

        public abstract void appendSwitchesAndArguments(java.lang.String[] array)
        Append switch/value items in "command line" format (excluding argv[0] program name). E.g. { '--gofast', '--username=fred' }
        参数:
        array - an array of switch or switch/value items in command line format. Unlike the other append routines, these switches SHOULD start with '--' . Unlike init(), this does not include the program name in array[0].

      • isNativeImplementation

        public boolean isNativeImplementation()
        Determine if the command line is bound to the native (JNI) implementation.
        返回:
        true if the underlying implementation is delegating to the native command line.

      • init

        public static void init(java.lang.String[] args)
        Initialize the singleton instance, must be called exactly once (either directly or via one of the convenience wrappers below) before using the static singleton instance.
        参数:
        args - command line flags in 'argv' format: args[0] is the program name.

      • initFromFile

        public static void initFromFile(java.lang.String file)
        Initialize the command line from the command-line file.
        参数:
        file - The fully qualified command line file.

      • reset

        public static void reset()
        Resets both the java proxy and the native command lines. This allows the entire command line initialization to be re-run including the call to onJniLoaded.

      • tokenizeQuotedAruments

        public static java.lang.String[] tokenizeQuotedAruments(char[] buffer)
        Public for testing (TODO: why are the tests in a different package?) Parse command line flags from a flat buffer, supporting double-quote enclosed strings containing whitespace. argv elements are derived by splitting the buffer on whitepace; double quote characters may enclose tokens containing whitespace; a double-quote literal may be escaped with back-slash. (Otherwise backslash is taken as a literal).
        参数:
        buffer - A command line in command line file format as described above.
        返回:
        the tokenized arguments, suitable for passing to init().
